    "The RCA network, as shown in Fig. 2, comprises five convolutional residual blocks, five channel attention blocks, an adaptive average pooling layer, and a fully connected layer.",
    "The main steps of the proposed scheme are described in the following subsections.",
    "Spatial feature detection backboneThis part is employed to extract features from various scales, and what's more, the residual connected structure interlinks the features from these various scales, resulting in better performance compared to conventional CNNs in representing the intricate semantic connections among multiscale objects in remote sensing images.",
    "CNNs have demonstrated exceptional abilities in representing features for scene classification tasks.",
    "Nevertheless, remote sensing scene datasets typically contain a limited number of images, and conventional CNN approaches often have a large number of parameters and shallow network layers."
